This paper is about federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the case where each participant has their own uniquely designed model, which suggests that it falls under the category of transfer learning. The use of knowledge distillation also suggests that it may fall under the category of model compression. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
